{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Only files changed in the pull request are analyzed — unchanged files are not scanned.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: a pure unit test of a filter function can miss failures in diff collection + path resolution wiring. REAL-INFRA: no real external network is required if we use a local git repo fixture and filesystem. MOCK-HIDE: mocking changed-file lists could hide incorrect git diff integration. So the minimum boundary is several modules wired together.","test_description":"Create a temporary git repo with a base commit and PR commit, change a subset of files, run the pipeline’s file-discovery + analysis flow end-to-end against the repo, and assert only changed paths are passed to analysis.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.18,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Findings are grouped by severity (error, warning, info) in the posted PR comment.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: grouping correctness often depends on parser/normalizer + formatter + comment payload builder, not one pure function. REAL-INFRA: no OS/network dependency is required to catch grouping failures; a local adapter stub is enough. MOCK-HIDE: fully mocking internal boundaries can hide schema mismatches between linter output and comment renderer.","test_description":"Run the analysis-to-comment rendering pipeline with mixed-severity findings and verify the generated PR comment body contains distinct error/warning/info sections with the expected findings under each.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.6,"System":0.13,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"A pull request that touches 200 files completes analysis within the 10-minute Actions timeout.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"REAL-INFRA: